  "text": "No statistically significant differences were noted in the sonographic abnormalities of hemiplegic shoulders of male and female subjects. This agrees with the results of previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and is probably due to the fact that shoulder anatomy in men and women is very similar. Therefore, changes due to aging or secondary to lesions such as stroke often present the same basic clinical or imaging pattern(s) in both sexes.",
